---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const lang = "en";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Paulina Velazquez" lang={lang} description="Privacy policy for the portfolio of Paulina Velazquez, Architect.">
  <Nav lang={lang} />

  <main class="w-full">
    <div class="flex w-full">
      <div class="hidden md:flex w-1/12 grid-line-v spacing-block"></div>
      <div class="w-full md:w-10/12 grid-line-v px-6 md:px-20 py-16 md:py-24 bg-canvas">
        <span class="text-[10px] font-mono opacity-40 uppercase tracking-[0.3em] mb-6 block">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-16 text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>

        <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-12 text-primary/70 font-light leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>When you contact Paulina Velazquez through this portfolio website, we may collect personal information you voluntarily provide, including your name, email address, phone number, and project details. We do not collect information automatically through cookies or tracking technologies beyond basic server logs.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>The information you provide is used exclusively to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-3 space-y-2">
              <li>Respond to your project inquiries and commission requests</li>
              <li>Communicate about potential architectural collaborations</li>
              <li>Provide estimates, proposals, and project-related documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">3. Information Sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or share your personal information with third parties. Your data may only be shared with collaborating professionals (engineers, consultants) directly involved in your project, and only with your prior consent.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">4. Data Retention</h2>
            <p>We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by applicable Mexican law (Ley Federal de Protección de Datos Personales en Posesión de los Particulares).</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">5. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>Under Mexican data protection law, you have the right to access, rectify, cancel, or oppose the processing of your personal data (ARCO rights). To exercise these rights, please contact us via email.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">6. Portfolio Content</h2>
            <p>All architectural works, drawings, renderings, and photographs displayed on this site are the intellectual property of Paulina Velazquez or used with permission. They are shown for portfolio and educational purposes only.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-primary mb-4 uppercase tracking-wide">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated revision date.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="pt-8 border-t border-gridLine">
            <p class="text-[10px] font-mono opacity-40 uppercase tracking-widest">Last updated — March 2026 · Mexico City, MX</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hidden md:block w-1/12 spacing-block"></div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
